cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the application of machine learning methods to the problem of beehive sound recognition. The primary focus is on exploring the potential of support vector machines and convolutional neural networks for this task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also involves the creation and release of annotations for a selection of beehive recordings, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Signal Processing). The use of machine learning methods for classification tasks is a common theme in the paper, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the development of beehive sound recognition systems, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques for data annotation, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
